{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17632721","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17632721"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:43:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:43:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17437"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17437","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17437"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10127"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70909"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10127","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10127"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17437"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56376"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5422"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23727"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23830"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70909","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70909"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EIntimate partner violence is a significant public health concern that affects individuals across all socioeconomic, cultural, and educational backgrounds.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a key risk factor for intimate partner violence?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Recent job loss or unemployment","Substance use by either partner","Social isolation from peers","History of previous relationships","Young age at marriage"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe strongest evidence-based risk factor for intimate partner violence is \u003Cstrong\u003Esubstance use by either partner\u003C/strong\u003E. Alcohol and drug use can impair judgement, increase aggression, and reduce inhibitions, leading to higher rates of violence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecent job loss or unemployment\u003C/strong\u003E: while financial stress can contribute to relationship tension, unemployment alone is not consistently identified as a primary risk factor.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESocial isolation from peers\u003C/strong\u003E: although social isolation may be a warning sign or consequence of abuse, it is not consistently identified as a primary risk factor.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHistory of previous relationships\u003C/strong\u003E: the number of previous relationships does not reliably predict intimate partner violence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EYoung age at marriage\u003C/strong\u003E: while age can be relevant, it is not consistently identified as a primary risk factor when compared to substance use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther significant risk factors include financial stress, history of childhood abuse, mental health issues, and previous exposure to violence. Healthcare providers should be aware that intimate partner violence can affect anyone, regardless of background.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Intimate partner violence affects approximately 1 in 4 women and occurs across all socioeconomic groups.","Key risk factors for intimate partner violence include substance use, financial stress, and history of childhood abuse.","Healthcare providers have a professional duty to screen for and respond appropriately to signs of intimate partner violence."],"references":["Corey J, Duggan M, Travers \u00c1. Risk and Protective Factors for Intimate Partner Violence Against Bisexual Victims: A Systematic Scoping Review. Trauma Violence Abuse. 2023;24(4):2130-2142. doi:10.1177/15248380221084749"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56376"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17437"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56376","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56376"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T15:09:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T15:10:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10127"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70909"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"5326","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5326"},"attributes":{"emoji":